Second wicket of the over and South Africa are bowled out for 287! No pace offered from Prasidh, Magala looks to loft it over covers but can only find K L Rahul, who makes no mistake. 3 wickets for Prasidh Krishna and India need 288 to win! Great comeback from India in the later stages of the innings as they pick up 7 wickets in the last 15 overs, giving away only 75 runs!

Terrific comeback with the ball from India as they are set a target of 288 runs. Quinton de Kock powered a fine century for South Africa, sharing a 144-run stand for the 4th wicket with Rassie van der Dussen before the Indian bowlers pegged them back from 214/3 to 287/10. Prasidh Krishna bagged 3/59, while Deepak Chahar and Jasprit Bumrah bagged 2 wickets each.
